data.description: Large 3 family with excellent cash flow. This brick 3 family offers over 3300 square feet on an extra long 25' x 150' lot. All units are rented and paying, but can be delivered vacant if necessary. Home is in good condition with recent renovations in some of the units. Only 4 blocks away is a highlight of the area, Highland Park, with it's many ball fields, tennis courts and the Ridgewood Reservoir. Directly across from the park is the North Brooklyn YMCA, (also 4 blocks). This home is very conveniently located close to many stores, bars, restaurants and other services on Fulton Street, only half a block away. These include Key Food Supermarket, (4 blocks), Pharmacy, (6 blocks), Laundromat, (only 1 block away), and many others. For easy transportation the J subway stop at Norwood Ave is only 2 blocks away and the A, C trains at Euclid Ave are only 10 blocks. Additionally, there are multiple busses within a few blocks of the home, (B13, Q24, Q56).
